1
2 (i) The people of Wyoming did "ordain and
3 establish" the Wyoming Constitution (Wyoming Constitution,
4 Preamble);
5
6 (ii) The Wyoming Legislature derives its powers
7 from the Wyoming Constitution and its acts must be conformable
8 to it:
9
10 Legislatures…[are] Creatures of the Constitution;
11 they owe their existence to the Constitution: they
12 derive their powers from the Constitution: it is
13 their commission; and, therefore, all their acts
14 must be conformable to it, or else they will be
15 void. Moore v. Harper, 600 U.S. 1 (2023) (internal
16 citations omitted);
17
18 (iii) Article 20, Section 1 of the Wyoming
19 Constitution provides that the Wyoming Constitution may be
20 amended, and specifies in what manner;
21
22 (iv) The apportionment provisions of the Wyoming
23 Constitution "are quite clear, explicit and mandatory…[and]
24 leave no room for confusion or doubt as to what the
25 legislature is to do about reapportionment and when it is to
26 do it." (State ex rel. Whitehead v. Gage, 377 P.2d 299, 301
27 (Wyo. 1963));
2
