1
2 (v) Article 3, Section 3 of the Wyoming
3 Constitution provides in relevant part:
4
5 Each county shall constitute a senatorial and
6 representative district; the senate and house of
7 representatives shall be composed of members
8 elected by the legal voters of the counties
9 respectively, every two (2) years. They shall be
10 apportioned among the said counties as nearly as
11 may be according to the number of their
12 inhabitants. Each county shall have at least one
13 senator and one representative; but at no time
14 shall the number of members of the house of
15 representatives be less than twice nor greater than
16 three times the number of members of the senate….
17 (Wyo. Const. Art. 3 sec. 3)
18
19 (vi) Article 3, Section 48 of the Wyoming
20 Constitution provides:
21
22 At the first budget session of the legislature
23 following the federal census, the legislature shall
24 reapportion its membership based upon that census.
25 Notwithstanding any other provision of this
26 article, any bill to apportion the legislature may
27 be introduced in a budget session in the same manner
28 as in a general session. (Wyo. Const. Art. 3 sec.
29 48)
30
31 (vii) Since 1992 the Wyoming Legislature, contrary
32 to Wyoming's constitutional apportionment provisions, has
33 allowed for the creation of legislative districts that do not
34 follow county lines and legislative districts that do not
3
