1 have at least one (1) representative and one (1) senator per
2 county;
3
4 (viii) Apportionment for the Wyoming Legislature
5 must also conform with the Equal Protection Clause of the 14th
6 Amendment under which the overriding objective is "that the
7 vote of any citizen is approximately equal in weight to that
8 of any other citizen in the State." (Reynolds v. Sims, 377
9 U.S. 533, 579 (1964));
10
11 (ix) Conformance to both the federal and state
12 constitutions may be best achieved with a legislature of
13 manageable size;
14
15 (x) No inconsistency exists between the
16 requirements of Wyoming Constitution Article 3, Sections 3
17 and 48 and those of the Equal Protection clause of the 14th
18 Amendment to the United States constitution and the Wyoming
19 Legislature must fully comply with both constitutions in
20 apportioning for legislative elections.
21
22 Section 2.
23
4
