1 (a) The Legislature further finds that:
2
3 (i) The Legislature shall make a good faith effort
4 to apportion itself as required by the 14th Amendment in
5 conformance with the principle that the vote of any citizen
6 is approximately equal in weight to that of any other citizen
7 in the State; and
8
9 (ii) The Legislature shall make a good faith
10 effort to apportion itself as required by Article 3, Section
11 3 and 48 of the Wyoming Constitution by providing for
12 legislative districts that follow county lines and
13 legislative districts that have at least one (1)
14 representative and one (1) senator per county.
15
16 Section 3. The Management Council of the Wyoming
17 Legislature shall assign a committee of the Legislature to
18 study apportionment of the Legislature as provided by this
19 act during the 2025 interim. The assigned committee shall
20 conduct meetings in communities around Wyoming to take input
21 on apportionment options from members of the public and other
22 interested stakeholders. The committee shall report its
23 findings to the Legislature not later than December 1, 2025.
